The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Bengal | Briefs
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                   BRIEFS
                  
	Calcutta, April 12: An 18-year-old boy on vacation was run over by a minibus on Mayo Road this afternoon.     
	Police said Tarun Baidya, who was walking with his friends along the tram tracks suddenly decided to cross the road, unmindful of the signal. The boy from Ghatakpukur in South 24-Parganas was in the middle of the road when the bus hit him.        
	Calcutta: The city police chief shuffled 51 inspectors on Saturday. The officers in charge of Karaya, Shakespeare Sarani, Burrabazar and Burtolla were changed.        
	Haldia: Sandalwood worth Rs 33 crore was found in containers about to be shipped from Haldia.     
	Airport arrest: A resident of Titagarh, North 24-Parganas, carrying stones worth Rs 18 lakh without valid papers was held in Calcutta airport. Tarakeswar Gupta had arrived on a Bangkok-Calcutta flight.         
	Calcutta: Seven pil-grims were killed in two mishaps. In Burdwan, a truck ran over four youths on a 55km trek with Ganga water. In South 24-Parganas Bishnupur, a truck hit a group going to Tarakeswar in Hooghly on foot. Uttara Adak, 35, Aparna Hati, 11, and Ashoka Patra, 40, died. The condition of two was serious.                                                                                                                                                                   
